div1.p:
Q. Did they say any thing about this boat-cloak? - A. James said they had a boat-cloak that would said, they had got it from Captain Wright's, and a man holloaed out to them from Captain Wright's window;
Benjamin James
said he answered, holloa! then they were pursued, and they had to leave the cloak in the field. He said, they had had some leaden pipe, and they were obliged to leave that.
